libthreadar
------------------------------------------
Libthreadar is a C++ library providing an abstracted set of C++ classes to
manipulate threads in a very simple and efficient way from your C++ code.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.5-1
  cygwin-devel-3.3.5-1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libstdc++6-11.3.0-1
  libthreadar-devel-1.4.0-1bl1
  libthreadar1000-1.4.0-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.8.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.38-1
  cygport-0.35.1-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  libtool-2.4.7-1
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://sourceforge.net/projects/libthreadar/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/libthreadar/libthreadar-1.4.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libthreadar-1.4.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libthreadar-1.4.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libthreadar-1.4.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libthreadar-1.4.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libthreadar1000-1.4.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libthreadar-devel-1.4.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libthreadar)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libthreadar.README
